Deferred/rejected-design log for the CTX project — spec authorship, tooling architecture (`ctx-verify`, `ctx-context`/formerly `ctx-access`, `ctx-cage`, `ctx-scan`, `ctx-brief`), and lint-policy history. Not a changelog of code; it is the *why*, including things tried and reversed. `intent.md` files point here instead of restating rationale; new entries are appended (never rewritten) as ADR-NNN, with later ADRs explicitly amending/superseding earlier ones by number.

Key structural facts an editor must know: many ADRs **supersede or amend** earlier ones by cross-reference (`[[ADR-NNN]]`) rather than replacing them — always check for a later amendment before treating an old entry as current (e.g. ADR-011 superseded in scope by ADR-022; ADR-024 amended by ADR-025; ADR-026/028/029/030/031 are a chain, corrected by ADR-032, resolved by ADR-033; ADR-034 rewrote the cage in Rust, later partly reworked by ADR-040/046/048/049; ADR-036/037/038 replaced the whole access-broker model with hook-based injection; ADR-051/052 retired `SPEC.md` itself). The single largest architectural pivot is documented across ADR-035 through ADR-038: CTX moved from enforcing context reading via a sandboxed cage + custom write tool (ADR-007/008/009/026) to a lead-by-hooks model where native Read/Edit trigger a `PostToolUse` hook that injects the rollup/intent chain, with the cage retained only as a safety boundary for autonomous runs (ADR-040/041/042).

Other load-bearing facts: leaf-summary line budgets and prompt style live in `prompts/summarizer-leaf.md` itself post-ADR-052 (not in this file); the `.ctxignore`-based scope matcher (ADR-044/045) is the sole authority for what gets summarized — `.gitignore` is only a one-time seed, never a live fallback; freshness is a SHA-256 content-hash tree (`hashes.json`, ADR-038), not git state; `ctx-verify`'s check-status precedence is `Errored > Fail > Skipped > Pass` (ADR-056) — a missing tool now fails the run rather than silently passing. Retired identifiers (`ctx-access`, `init-task`, `end-task`, `served_nodes`) are grep-banned outside this file and `docs/retired/**` (ADR-051). When editing code touched by an ADR, check here first for rejected alternatives before re-proposing them.